rComments: Great prof who really knows what he's talking about. Took his Beatle's class and it was probably the best course I'll ever take in my life. Was a Beatles fan before, but an even bigger one after I took his class because of the enthusiasm he showed for the band. Essays were very interesting and there was no boring work in his class.
Not a fan. Inconsistent grader.

Professor himself is alright; lectures are pleasant to listen to because of his British accent. However, the course itself is a complete waste of time and is heavily revolved around "India" because that's where he spent most of his life. Course is absolutely useless and listenings and quizzes are stupid. Don't take this course.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: This was one of my favourite classes of the year. Kippen gets a lot of crap from lazy narrow-minded performance majors who don't think it's important to learn about anything beyond Western music, but his lectures were engaging and the listening examples were very interesting. He's a little too hung up on the Beatles though, not a fan of that.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: It was a great pleasure attending his lecture. He knows his stuff and presents it well. Great flexibility in terms of topics when it comes to assignments.
I like his accent. Very knowledgable in the subject, funny, and appears enthusiastic at every lecture.
He's awesome.

Prof. Kippen is phenomenal.  He loves what he teaches and it really shows.  He's no pushover but he recognizes hard work and brings such passion to what he teaches that students really want to make an effort.  He's kind of understated and cool, and you can hear a pin drop in his classes.

First of all I would like to thank James Kippen for teaching a course entirely on the BEATLES!!! What a great prof! You couldn't ask for more. He kept class interesting with lots of videos and music.. anthologies too! Essays are worth 65% of the grade which is great for those who arent the best at writing exams! Very Helpful when you ask for it!

What can I say?  I have never enjoyed listening to a prof this much - he has the HOTTEST voice!  Very knowledgable and succinct.  He seemed genuinely intersted in what he was teaching too (World Music) which helped sustain my interest!

The first couple of lectures were AMAZING (Beatles!). After a few weeks, I got bored of the whole Indian tabla thing. Yes- he is very knowledgeable, but only about Indian music! Music and society is supposed to reflect all societies...not just India! He also seemed extremely arrogant and BRITISH. I liked the accent though...
An awesome lecturer.  I loved the class, the material was really interesting and he was engaging.  He definitely knows his stuff.
Amazingly knowledgeable, yet approachable and clear. If you work hard and produce quality work, he will reward you generously. But watch out - he does have high standards inspite of seeming relaxed.

This was an interesting course and Prof. Kippen presents a lot of valuable and new material. A basic understanding of many cultural musics is gained through this course. It is clear that Kippen has a vast wealth of knowledge and experience to draw on for this course. He is a very interesting lecturer to learn from.
Really really interesting lecturer, with interesting material and presentation. Also really helpful and nice. Love the accent :)

Excellent lecturer, very well organized and interesting. He really wanted people to learn, and his assignments and tests reflected the ways he wanted to challenge people to make them better. Love the accent!!
he is generally a good lecturer and for the most part the tests and assignments are a logical extension of course material
He really knows his stuff, and his lectures are lively and interesting. But too much foreign vocabs to learn, there should be a test to prep ourselves before the exam.
Not a bad prof
Course is interesting most times, yet main points are muddled by numerous non important information. Tough marker yet i wish he would be more specific with his answers to papers, and questions.
No Comments
His english accent made 9AM classes very interesting...so hot....
Awesome prof, knows his stuff, but even better, he knows his stus & how they wor
Very professional, well prepared and intelligent. Course is a tuffie though!
